# docs — Architecture & Documentation

This is `movie-finder-docs` (`docs/`) — all architecture diagrams, ADRs, and project documentation.
GitHub repo: `aharbii/movie-finder-docs` · Tracker: `aharbii/movie-finder`

## What this submodule contains

```
docs/architecture/
├── plantuml/          # PlantUML .puml files — canonical UML source
│   ├── 01-domain-model.puml
│   ├── 02-system-architecture.puml
│   ├── 03-backend-architecture.puml
│   ├── 04-langgraph-pipeline.puml
│   ├── 05-langgraph-statemachine.puml
│   ├── 06-frontend-architecture.puml
│   ├── 07-seq-authentication.puml
│   ├── 08-seq-chat-sse.puml
│   ├── 09-seq-langgraph-execution.puml
│   └── 10-deployment-azure.puml
├── workspace.dsl      # Structurizr C4 — L1/L2/L3 + deployment views
└── decisions/         # Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)
    └── index.md       # ADR template + index
```

## Rendering

```bash
# From repo root:
make mkdocs        # full build → http://localhost:8001
make structurizr   # C4 live view → http://localhost:18080

# VSCode: Alt+D / Option+D for PlantUML live preview (jebbs.plantuml)
```

## Rules

- **PlantUML is the canonical UML source** — always update `.puml` files, never `.mdj`
- **Structurizr DSL** (`workspace.dsl`) — update for any container, component, or relation change
- **ADRs** — write one for every new tech decision, dependency, or project-wide pattern change
- PNGs are gitignored — generated at build time by the mkdocs container

## Personas available

Architect is the primary persona here. Type `/architect` or use `@architect` in Cursor chat.
Other personas: `/mentor` (explain architecture), `/reviewer` (review doc changes), `/pm` (create issues).
